The paper proposes a method for generating video-realistic animations of real humans using a neural network. The method involves tracking the 3D motion of the person in the video using a template model and generating a synthetically rendered version of the video. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves training a conditional generative adversarial network, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves generating video results, which suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
